definitions.definition: Pronounced with an audible breath , a brief expulsion of air at the end of the sound.
examples: In English, word-initial single voiceless consonants are aspirated , so that pit is pronounced [pʰɪt] but spit is pronounced [spɪt] .

definitions.definition: In French , describing an initial letter h which, though silent, does not permit liaison or elision with the preceding word.
examples: The h in haine is aspirated , so one says la haine , not l'haine .

main_definition: ( phonetics ) Pronounced with an audible breath , a brief expulsion of air at the end of the sound.
